Loop iter (2026-05-25): ROOT-CAUSED + FIXED the cascade build-provenance bug (rs-plugkit 0905378). Symptom: pushed+CI-green commits (e.g. e17696d codesearch autobuild) absent from the published wasm (0.1.562 ran pre-autobuild code despite git ancestry guaranteeing the source was in the tree). ROOT CAUSE found by reading release.yml: the Build job uses Swatinem/rust-cache@v2 with a CONSTANT key 'release-wasm32-wasip1', which restores target/ including a stale target/wasm32-wasip1/release/rs_plugkit.wasm + incremental fingerprints. After restore, cargo's incremental judgment skips recompiling the top crate, and the Rename step cp's the CACHED STALE wasm to plugkit.wasm — so the published artifact doesn't reflect the pushed source, with green CI. FIX: before cargo build, 'rm -f target/.../rs_plugkit.wasm' + 'cargo clean --release --target wasm32-wasip1 -p rs-plugkit' to force a fresh top-crate compile, plus a post-build existence check. Correctness over cache speed for shipped artifacts. SECONDARY risk documented (PRD bump-rebase-theirs-can-drop-source, out-of-reach): the bump job's 'git rebase -s recursive -X theirs origin/main' could revert a raced source change while keeping the version bump. IMPLICATION FOR PAST WORK: any prior 'pushed + CI-built, validation gated on cascade' resolution may have validated against a stale binary — re-validate codesearch autobuild + any other cascade-gated fix once a release built with 0905378 publishes (version > 0.1.562). Validated live on 0.1.562 this session: slug-alias + memorize-prune work.